WEBVTT

00:02.535 --> 00:04.469
ANNOUNCER:
<i>December 17, 1989.</i>

00:04.471 --> 00:05.870
<i>History is made.</i>

00:05.872 --> 00:07.139
<i>America says hello</i>

00:07.141 --> 00:09.041
<i>to the first</i>
<i>non-prehistoric family</i>

00:09.043 --> 00:10.742
<i>in primetime animation.</i>

00:10.744 --> 00:13.678
[BART SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

00:13.680 --> 00:15.980
<i>January 12, 1997.</i>

00:15.982 --> 00:17.382
<i>History isn't done.</i>

00:17.384 --> 00:19.017
King of the Hill <i>premieres,</i>

00:19.019 --> 00:20.852
<i>taking America</i>
<i>by light drizzle.</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:23.655
HANK:
<i>I sell propane.</i>

00:24.790 --> 00:27.325
ANNOUNCER:
<i>January 31, 1999.</i>

00:27.327 --> 00:29.094
<i>Knock-knock. Who's there?</i>

00:29.096 --> 00:32.363
<i>It's history again</i>
<i>as</i> Family Guy <i>premieres.</i>

00:32.365 --> 00:34.532
[STEWIE SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

00:34.534 --> 00:38.136
<i>And then history makes</i>
<i>its first mistake in history.</i>

00:38.138 --> 00:40.004
<i>It cancels</i> Family Guy.

00:42.208 --> 00:44.342
<i>August 12, 2004.</i>

00:44.344 --> 00:47.528
<i>Eric Hammel, a misogynistic</i>
<i>pothead loner from Cincinnati</i>

00:47.530 --> 00:50.698
<i>walks into a store</i>
<i>and buys a</i> Family Guy <i>DVD.</i>

00:50.700 --> 00:53.101
<i>History is listening.</i>

00:53.103 --> 00:54.385
American Dad! <i>is also a show.</i>

00:54.387 --> 00:56.387
<i>But tonight,</i>
<i>the biggest history</i>

00:56.389 --> 00:58.723
<i>in the history of history</i>
<i>will be made.</i>

00:58.725 --> 01:00.592
<i>Because,</i>
<i>for the first time ever,</i>

01:00.594 --> 01:02.861
<i>primetime animation</i>
<i>will be going</i>

01:02.863 --> 01:04.228
<i>live.</i>

01:04.230 --> 01:07.265
<i>From Fox Studios,</i>
<i>in Century City, California,</i>

01:07.267 --> 01:11.319
<i>it's the first-ever live</i>
<i>telecast of an animated series.</i>

01:11.321 --> 01:15.056
<i>This is</i>
The Cleveland Show Live,

01:15.058 --> 01:17.876
<i>with special guest star,</i>
<i>Julia Roberts.</i>

01:17.878 --> 01:19.694
<i>Brought to you by Circuit City.</i>

01:19.696 --> 01:23.331
<i>Circuit City, there's one left.</i>
<i>Come find us.</i>

01:23.333 --> 01:25.233
<i>Featuring the Walter Murphy</i>
<i>Orchestra.</i>

01:29.071 --> 01:32.741
<i>And now, an overweight,</i>
<i>bumbling cartoon dad,</i>

01:32.743 --> 01:36.211
<i>Cleveland Brown.</i>

01:36.213 --> 01:38.713
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

01:38.715 --> 01:41.015
♪ And I am proud to be

01:41.017 --> 01:43.201
♪ Right back for season two

01:43.203 --> 01:46.087
♪ With my new family

01:46.089 --> 01:50.725
Ladies and gentlemen,
the original Solid Gold Dancers.

01:52.461 --> 01:54.696
♪ There's old friends
And new friends ♪

01:54.698 --> 01:56.898
♪ And even a bear

01:56.900 --> 01:59.484
♪ Through good times
And bad times ♪

01:59.486 --> 02:01.019
♪ It's true love we share ♪

02:01.021 --> 02:03.154
♪ And so I found a place

02:03.156 --> 02:05.457
♪ Where I don't take no jive ♪

02:05.459 --> 02:07.842
♪ Screw <i>The Amazing Race</i> ♪

02:07.844 --> 02:10.144
♪ You're watching
<i>Cleveland Live</i> ♪

02:10.146 --> 02:11.913
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

02:11.915 --> 02:13.247
Thank you.

02:13.249 --> 02:14.666
<i>Thank you.</i>

02:14.668 --> 02:17.902
[CHEERING]

02:20.355 --> 02:22.223
Whoop, here I is.

02:22.225 --> 02:25.760
That's gonna be my new
catchphrase for season two.

02:25.762 --> 02:29.146
Mine's gonna be
"Teddy bear picnic."

02:29.148 --> 02:30.482
You know what? Forget it.

02:30.484 --> 02:32.016
Catchphrases are stupid.

02:32.018 --> 02:34.369
Party over here.

02:34.371 --> 02:36.304
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

02:36.306 --> 02:38.172
Boys, I--

02:39.841 --> 02:42.843
Boys, I need--

02:42.845 --> 02:45.346
Boys, I need you
to go pack your things.

02:45.348 --> 02:47.682
You'll be spending the night
at Robert's apartment.

02:47.684 --> 02:49.450
Dad's place? All right.

02:49.452 --> 02:51.653
I bet he takes me
to the outdoor mall

02:51.655 --> 02:53.921
so I can drum
on buckets for change.

02:53.923 --> 02:55.823
[SCATTING]

02:57.425 --> 02:58.994
Now, that's funky.

02:58.996 --> 03:02.180
Dad, are we being sent to
Robert's to scare us straight?

03:02.182 --> 03:04.115
No, I paid Robert to watch you

03:04.117 --> 03:07.252
so Donna and I can have
the place to ourselves.

03:07.254 --> 03:08.703
It's our first anniversary

03:08.705 --> 03:11.405
and I've planned
a big romantic dinner,

03:11.407 --> 03:12.841
which could very well lead

03:12.843 --> 03:16.344
to slow dancing,
the recitation of love poetry

03:16.346 --> 03:19.981
and other things that are
too taboo to be discussed.

03:19.983 --> 03:21.082
[CHUCKLES]

03:21.084 --> 03:22.350
If I were Bernie Mac

03:22.352 --> 03:24.386
I'd be sitting
in a chair right now

03:24.388 --> 03:26.687
telling America
how stupid you are.

03:26.689 --> 03:29.290
Miss you, Bernie.

03:32.044 --> 03:35.880
Hey, Roberta, are you staying
at your deadbeat dad's too?

03:35.882 --> 03:39.367
Please, if I wanted to breathe
toxic mold and get flea bites

03:39.369 --> 03:42.570
I'd date Zach Galifianakis.

03:42.572 --> 03:46.491
It's gonna happen
one way or the other.

03:47.927 --> 03:50.395
Roberta's staying
at her friend Tassie's house.

03:50.397 --> 03:52.530
You know, the Iranian one.

03:52.532 --> 03:56.034
Because ayatollah
her to get lost.

03:56.036 --> 03:57.101
[LAUGHS]

03:57.103 --> 03:59.404
No, but it's gonna
work out great.

03:59.406 --> 04:00.771
Donna's gonna be so supr--

04:00.773 --> 04:03.408
MAN:
You're fat.

04:03.410 --> 04:05.910
You know what else is fat?

04:05.912 --> 04:08.813
Rudeness.

04:08.815 --> 04:11.081
[♪]

04:13.485 --> 04:15.453
Hey, you kids like games, right?

04:15.455 --> 04:17.254
Well, I got a fun one for you.

04:17.256 --> 04:20.358
It's called Open the Box,
Take Out the DVD Player

04:20.360 --> 04:23.594
Put a Brick Where it Was,
And Then Tape it Back Up.

04:23.596 --> 04:27.115
And then we can build a wall
out of the DVD players. Yay!

04:27.117 --> 04:28.316
[TIRES SCREECH]

04:28.318 --> 04:31.018
Oh, no, they found me.

04:31.020 --> 04:33.321
Quick, move.
Out the back window.

04:34.890 --> 04:36.891
Man, we're three stories up.

04:36.893 --> 04:38.960
It's okay, the dumpster
will break our fall.

04:38.962 --> 04:40.494
But I'm scared, Daddy.

04:40.496 --> 04:42.897
I'm not your daddy, fool.
Let's split.

04:42.899 --> 04:45.933
Here I go.

04:45.935 --> 04:47.368
[CLATTERING]

04:47.370 --> 04:50.537
To infinity and beyond.

04:50.539 --> 04:51.806
[CLATTERING]

04:51.808 --> 04:53.407
Guess it's my turn.

04:53.409 --> 04:55.542
[YELLS]

04:55.544 --> 04:57.611
[CLATTERING]

04:57.613 --> 05:00.097
[♪]

05:01.967 --> 05:03.601
Anthony.

05:04.670 --> 05:06.237
Let's see, I'll sit here

05:06.239 --> 05:08.306
and I guess the most natural
thing would be

05:08.308 --> 05:12.076
for Donna to sit next to me
also facing in that direction.

05:12.078 --> 05:14.045
You can come in now, Donna.

05:16.515 --> 05:19.417
Cleveland,
you made all this?

05:19.419 --> 05:22.187
And you're gonna clean it all up
by yourself afterwards?

05:22.189 --> 05:23.387
Whatever.

05:23.389 --> 05:25.156
Now, let's get to work

05:25.158 --> 05:28.159
on making those legs wobbly.

05:30.913 --> 05:34.816
Look at me, I'm totally nude.

05:36.985 --> 05:39.253
Looks like I've got
some catching up to do

05:39.255 --> 05:42.457
behind this pillar
we've always had.

05:43.926 --> 05:45.225
MAN:
Boobs.

05:47.228 --> 05:49.480
Eek!
Robert?

05:49.482 --> 05:52.867
There's some bad stuff
going down. Real bad.

05:52.869 --> 05:54.535
These people
don't mess around.

05:54.537 --> 05:57.105
I'm gonna have to lay low here
for a couple of days.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.940
No, absolutely not.

05:58.942 --> 06:02.910
It's our first anniversary,
the paper anniversary.

06:02.912 --> 06:05.880
I was gonna give her an index
card on which I'd written:

06:05.882 --> 06:08.183
"I'd marry you all over again."

06:08.185 --> 06:11.336
Wait a minute, there's no reason
I still can't give it to you.

06:11.338 --> 06:12.704
Here you go.

06:12.706 --> 06:14.539
Aw.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.708
WOMAN:
You got a good one, girl.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.243
[GROANING]

06:18.245 --> 06:21.011
Please, don't let my daddy
get killed, Cleveland.

06:21.013 --> 06:23.781
You can't be
my only male role model.

06:23.783 --> 06:27.518
I'll grow up to be
an overweight gay loser.

06:27.520 --> 06:30.688
That's crazy talk, sugar.

06:30.690 --> 06:32.874
Cleveland,
he's in a lot of trouble.

06:32.876 --> 06:34.575
We don't have a choice.

06:34.577 --> 06:35.727
[CHUCKLES]

06:35.729 --> 06:39.864
Hey, looks like C-Brown
just got C-blocked.

06:39.866 --> 06:41.899
Time to get strapped, doughboy.

06:41.901 --> 06:43.867
Pardon me?
Get your gun ready.

06:43.869 --> 06:45.470
I don't have a gun.

06:45.472 --> 06:48.306
I used to live here.
We got guns everywhere.

06:48.308 --> 06:50.141
Flip the couch.

06:53.462 --> 06:55.863
I don't even
need to buy bullets

06:55.865 --> 06:59.767
because I'm sweating them.
Sheesh.

06:59.769 --> 07:01.019
MAN 1:
And we're clear.

07:01.021 --> 07:02.186
[BELL RINGS]

07:02.188 --> 07:04.689
Okay, where's the guy
who said I was fat?

07:04.691 --> 07:06.724
MAN 2:
Right here.

07:08.827 --> 07:10.962
And apparently,
the props department

07:10.964 --> 07:13.330
has put real bullets
in our guns.

07:13.332 --> 07:14.999
Sorry about that.

07:15.001 --> 07:18.470
ANNOUNCER:
The Cleveland Show Live
<i>will be right back.</i>

07:23.492 --> 07:25.109
[CLEVELAND SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

07:25.111 --> 07:29.781
Robert and Rallo, places for
act two. Robert and Rallo.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.148
[LAUGHING]

07:34.987 --> 07:37.154
[♪]

07:47.549 --> 07:49.216
Someone's coming, get ready.

07:50.735 --> 07:52.070
Honey, I'm--
Now.

07:52.072 --> 07:55.106
My tibias. Ah!
There's a sack on my head.

07:55.108 --> 07:56.975
Get it off, get if off,
get it off.

07:56.977 --> 07:58.709
I think it's Cleveland.

07:58.711 --> 08:01.529
Or someone who sounds like
Cleveland sent here to fool us.

08:01.531 --> 08:03.164
CLEVELAND:
No, it's me.

08:03.166 --> 08:05.800
My fibulas.

08:05.802 --> 08:07.952
Donna, that man is--

08:10.789 --> 08:13.490
Sure is windy in here.

08:13.492 --> 08:15.960
Donna, that man
is a nuisance and a menace

08:15.962 --> 08:18.395
and he's putting our family
in danger.

08:18.397 --> 08:19.731
He has to go.

08:19.733 --> 08:24.401
The only Robert I want to see
around here is Julia Roberts.

08:26.021 --> 08:28.439
Look, Cleveland, Robert's
the father of my children.

08:28.441 --> 08:30.975
So unless you can come
up with another safe place,

08:30.977 --> 08:32.276
he's staying with us.

08:32.278 --> 08:34.111
Oh, but I was gonna do

08:34.113 --> 08:36.514
a makeup anniversary
dinner tonight.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.383
I got filet mignon.

08:38.385 --> 08:41.118
I'm sorry, honey.

08:41.120 --> 08:45.790
Oh, I guess I'll have to save
that filet for later.

08:45.792 --> 08:48.426
MAN:
Boo. I mean, yay.

08:53.382 --> 08:56.384
Man, Cleveland, you skipped
fun drunk and sad drunk

08:56.386 --> 08:58.219
and went straight
to angry drunk.

08:58.221 --> 08:59.620
You'd be angry too

08:59.622 --> 09:03.358
if your wife's ex-husband
was sleeping on your couch.

09:06.912 --> 09:08.712
MAN [WHISPERING]:
<i>Houseguest.</i> Sinbad.

09:08.714 --> 09:10.681
Housebad.

09:10.683 --> 09:11.966
Thank you.

09:11.968 --> 09:15.236
I just wish I could find
somewhere else for Robert to go.

09:15.238 --> 09:17.938
That guy living in my house
is more out of place

09:17.940 --> 09:20.541
than I would be as an
aristocratic woman

09:20.543 --> 09:22.743
in 18th century France.

09:24.646 --> 09:26.430
[BAROQUE MUSIC PLAYING
ON HARPSICORD]

09:31.069 --> 09:33.971
Warning, don't go
in the toilette.

09:33.973 --> 09:36.874
After eating all
those heavy French pastries

09:36.876 --> 09:41.012
I've turned the bidet
into a bi-don't.

09:43.965 --> 09:47.034
So, yeah, Robert
doesn't belong in my house.

09:47.036 --> 09:50.304
Look, Cleveland, Robert has come
to you in his time of need

09:50.306 --> 09:53.541
and you have to be a good
Christian and help him.

09:53.543 --> 09:57.344
I know it's hard but
you gotta just suck it off.

09:57.346 --> 09:58.379
Fine.

09:58.381 --> 10:00.748
If you're such
a good Christian, Tim,

10:00.750 --> 10:02.717
why don't you take him in?

10:02.719 --> 10:03.850
Me?

10:03.852 --> 10:07.088
It's not really a good time
for us, you know.

10:07.090 --> 10:09.923
A couple of periods ago,
Arianna went crazy

10:09.925 --> 10:11.858
and tore up the mattress
in the guest room.

10:11.860 --> 10:14.562
Hi, Jesus,
it's me, Cleveland.

10:14.564 --> 10:18.099
I know I haven't talked to you
since Donna's pregnancy scare

10:18.101 --> 10:21.335
but I need to tell you a little
something about my friend Tim,

10:21.337 --> 10:23.637
who I thought
was a good Christian.

10:23.639 --> 10:26.307
Oh, come on,
don't bust me to Jesus.

10:26.309 --> 10:28.008
Well?

10:28.010 --> 10:30.844
All right, I guess
I should papa what I preach.

10:32.214 --> 10:34.215
If you're going
to be hiding out with us,

10:34.217 --> 10:35.916
you must put on a shirt.

10:35.918 --> 10:38.119
Nobody wants to see
your pumped-up muscles

10:38.121 --> 10:39.620
and prison scars.

10:39.622 --> 10:43.124
What's wrong, you getting
turned on? You can't handle it?

10:43.126 --> 10:44.558
Oh, please.

10:44.560 --> 10:46.060
I wouldn't handle it

10:46.062 --> 10:48.729
wearing the thickest
of my gardening gloves.

10:48.731 --> 10:50.231
And put that out.

10:50.233 --> 10:52.967
This is a smoke-free household.

10:52.969 --> 10:55.853
Lady, you sure got
a lot of rules.

10:57.005 --> 10:58.589
[GROWLS]

10:58.591 --> 11:01.759
"Grr" yourself, bear bitch.

11:03.962 --> 11:06.697
Call me a bitch again.

11:14.155 --> 11:16.407
[WHISTLING]

11:21.547 --> 11:22.913
Brisk.

11:22.915 --> 11:25.899
Whoa, whose funeral
are you all dressed up for?

11:25.901 --> 11:28.318
Please, say my dentist.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.654
That was an ad-lib.

11:29.656 --> 11:32.156
I should be getting paid
to write this show too.

11:32.158 --> 11:35.526
And y'all never got back to me
about directing that episode.

11:35.528 --> 11:36.677
I'm dressed up

11:36.679 --> 11:38.646
because your mother and I
are finally having

11:38.648 --> 11:39.981
our anniversary dinner.

11:39.983 --> 11:41.983
Here, go see a movie.

11:41.985 --> 11:44.284
Nothing with boobs.
Aw.

11:44.286 --> 11:47.655
And nothing with elves.
Aw.

11:51.627 --> 11:53.244
Mm-mm.

11:53.246 --> 11:58.215
This place is dark, romantic
and smells like fondue,

11:58.217 --> 12:00.017
just like my man.

12:00.019 --> 12:02.586
Happy anniversa--

12:02.588 --> 12:08.092
Roberta, what a surprise to see
you here at this particular time

12:08.094 --> 12:10.328
and not entering
through the door

12:10.330 --> 12:12.629
but through this fourth wall
of our house.

12:12.631 --> 12:14.898
Well, I thought I'd stop by

12:14.900 --> 12:17.734
because apparently I've been
over at Tassie's

12:17.736 --> 12:20.071
for three days now.

12:20.073 --> 12:21.439
Uh, you have?

12:21.441 --> 12:23.774
Yeah, but I guess somebody
didn't think of that

12:23.776 --> 12:27.678
when he cut my story
out of the show, remember?

12:27.680 --> 12:30.914
Roberta takes
the debate team to regionals?

12:30.916 --> 12:33.651
Yeah, that was a laugh riot.
Set your VCR.

12:33.653 --> 12:36.320
Nobody uses VCRs anymore, fool.

12:36.322 --> 12:38.823
How do you play tapes?

12:40.074 --> 12:41.175
[GASPS]

12:42.810 --> 12:44.144
[CLEARS THROAT]

12:44.146 --> 12:46.646
I wonder who's at the door.

12:46.648 --> 12:48.048
Right now.

12:48.050 --> 12:49.316
[DOORBELL RINGS]

12:49.318 --> 12:51.235
Oh, it's Tim.

12:51.237 --> 12:53.337
Tim,
what are you doing here?

12:53.339 --> 12:55.072
Arianna. Robert.

12:55.074 --> 12:56.974
I-- I walked in on them.

12:56.976 --> 12:59.810
They were playing
Hide The Salman Rushdie.

12:59.812 --> 13:01.012
What?

13:01.014 --> 13:02.646
First, he did it regular style.

13:02.648 --> 13:04.949
And then he did it
like an NBA guy,

13:04.951 --> 13:08.352
right on top of our
Energy Star-qualified washer

13:08.354 --> 13:09.619
from Circuit City.

13:09.621 --> 13:11.405
Say, Tim,
how much does that

13:11.407 --> 13:13.640
Energy Star-qualified washer

13:13.642 --> 13:15.876
from Circuit City
tend to save you

13:15.878 --> 13:17.545
on your utility bills?

13:17.547 --> 13:20.548
As much as $200 a year.

13:20.550 --> 13:22.332
Not too shabby.

13:24.803 --> 13:28.105
Anyway, Arianna said
she doesn't love me anymore.

13:28.107 --> 13:30.041
She said Robert
is everything I'm not.

13:30.043 --> 13:31.742
Strong and virile,

13:31.744 --> 13:36.547
and he doesn't cry after,
so you know, yay for Robert.

13:36.549 --> 13:38.615
Cleveland,
this is your fault.

13:38.617 --> 13:41.068
You told him
to tear up my wife?

13:41.070 --> 13:44.905
No, sir, I wouldn't--
ROBERTA: Don't mind me.

13:44.907 --> 13:48.141
I'm just gonna start
my own after-party here.

13:48.143 --> 13:50.977
You know, because
the show's over for me

13:50.979 --> 13:54.281
since my
debate story got cut.

13:54.283 --> 13:55.449
[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

13:55.451 --> 13:58.152
Roberta, I don't think
you should be drinking

13:58.154 --> 14:00.521
since you're only 15.

14:00.523 --> 14:03.324
I play 15, jackass.

14:03.326 --> 14:06.794
All right, seems
like Roberta's not feeling well

14:06.796 --> 14:09.296
so maybe she should go
to the doctor and--

14:09.298 --> 14:12.265
Maybe you
should go to hell.

14:12.267 --> 14:13.334
Don't you touch me.

14:13.336 --> 14:14.902
Okay, Settle down.
I'm a survivor.

14:14.904 --> 14:16.270
And you know why?
I can do it all.

14:16.272 --> 14:18.572
Live episode, remember,
this affects us.

14:18.574 --> 14:20.808
I'm every woman.
Studio execs are watching.

14:20.810 --> 14:23.243
I was in <i>Hustle & Flow.</i>
Wanna be in the movie?

14:23.245 --> 14:25.546
Back off, old man.
You might wanna play ball.

14:25.548 --> 14:28.081
Go to commercial.
Go to commercial.

14:31.319 --> 14:32.786
